metadata.name: Kinetics #267
metadata.description:
CONTROLS
 * Pause a Kinetic by clicking on the canvas.
 * Increase and decrease the p5js framerate by tapping the left and right arrows.
 * Pause the top layer by tapping down arrow.
 * Save a frame by tapping S.
 * Press H for High Quality, M for Default, L for Low Quality. Note, this effects performance.
 * Reset the Kinetic by by tapping backspace.

Kinetics is a neo-constructivist generative art project built using p5js. Each Kinetic delicately moves from it's origin, giving the appearance of infinite space and possibility. The viewer witnesses the construction of the Kinetic floating inside of the negative. Shapes and lines move around the Kinetic in a dazzling display of contrasting color.

The texture developed for Kinetics, deemed The Creation of the Universe (See top right) is at its core a color gradient of 3 different colors. Each piece construct's itself, drawing lines on top of lines to create a unique self contained assembly of materials as opposed to a realistic abstraction. The Creation of the Universe repeats itself in each piece, just as cells do in an organic structure. From here is where it initially got it's name.

Inspired heavily by the works of Rodchenko and Tatlin, each Kinetic appears to slot together like a puzzle. Each piece has multiple hard edge planes clashing aggressively with each other giving the sense that there is more than just a flat canvas. A quasi realism is created through our desire to build instead of simply paint.

"Long Live Generative Art"

- Mitchell

metadata.name: Furry #136
metadata.description:
Experiments in textures and deconstructing the 2D/3D perspective.

Instructions:
- use the mouse to navigate (zoom, pan and drag)
- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 'b' to switch on/off the background color (in case you want to print it)
- press 'p' to download the current view it in a custom resolution (only in live view).

Berlin, December 2021
@bgola

metadata.name: Euphonic #1279
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: Resilience  #219
metadata.description:
Resilience is a collection of endless architectures.
In a resilient generative system composed of multiple compatible parts, real-time information exchange enables open reconfigurations and continuous discrete adjustments. Sometimes vague and fuzzy, sometimes real and tangible, they reveal different readings of architectural complexity and scale: from city plans to floor plans and details to sections and elevations.

Resilience comes in a variety of polychrome palettes, ascii glyphs, and styles. 
To enjoy it in full-screen mode, press the left mouse button in live mode, for a monochrome look press 'b'. Made with P5js.

Resilience Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022

metadata.name: Festival #37
metadata.description:
In the meta color space of the digital light spectrum, red, green, and blue lived peacefully.

But then, a being from beyond (BFB) stirred up the colors and started to apply functions and functions upon functions. Red, green, and blue grew tired and weary of the manipulation and broke up into weird random structures.

The BFB was disheartened, but realising the colors pains, searched for more simple harmonies between the colors, and applied endless variations to tease vibrancy into the life of the colors. The colors rewarded the BFB with Festival, their dance of joy. 

Made with p5js, a bit of math and plenty of experimentation. Gold is rare, super high or low density is rare.

metadata.name: Guiding Light / Lost in Stillness #10
metadata.description:
Sometimes one can be lost. Not knowing where to go, frozen to action, as if any movement could be fatal against the unknown.

Then it all clicks. It may be due to a new tought, or due to the words of a loved one, it may even click thanks to the beauty of a flock of birds flying against the sky.
With a clear destination and renewed courage, the once lost can now resume their journey.


---

Made in Cables.gl


Press "P" to save a 15 second .webm video

Process can be a little wonky, and unfortunately only webm support

metadata.name: Triangular Dreams #31
metadata.description:
Delaunay triangulation is a good old resource in the generative toolbox. In this work I’ve tried to give it a new twist, combining it with different methods to place points in space, and filling each triangle with lines that go from one corner to the opposite side. The goal is to generate a wide range of semi-abstract scenes, that can sometimes be reminiscent of the work of Paul Klee, Lyonel Feininger or other Bauhaus members.

Controls:
[c] to switch between 3 color modes: color mixes, color zones and monochrome
[f] to toggle fullscreen
[s] to save a screen capture
[2] to [9] to generate and save a hi-res image at 2x, 3x, … your viewport size

This work will adapt nicely to any screen format.
No palettes have been used, it is all random colors within a certain hue and saturation range.
Made with p5.js and d3.js
